# # ============================================================================
# # NOTES
# # ============================================================================
# # - Ghostty doesn't have a direct equivalent to tmux's "join-pane" or "break-pane"
# #   These would require moving splits between tabs, which isn't currently supported
# # - The "p=set status" binding is mapped to toggle_window_decorations
# # - New splits don't inherit the current directory by default in Ghostty
# #   This is a limitation compared to tmux's -c "#{pane_current_path}"
# # - Tab overview can be toggled with: ctrl+space>o (if you want to add it)
# #   keybind = ctrl+space>o=toggle_tab_overview
